# Project hints (agent)

This solution is iterated over a long time—**preserve earned knowledge**.

1. **Before** many retries on the same build, test, or tool command, **skim** `.cursor/project-hints.md`.
2. After **several failed attempts** you find a **non-obvious** fix (locks, config, flags, paths, environment), **append one line** to that file.
3. **Format:** `- ` + single line, **≤ ~120 characters**, no paragraph. Skip typos and one-shot mistakes. Do not duplicate an existing hint; update the closest line if the tip changes.
4. If the fix is a **repeatable multi-step workflow** (not a one-liner), add or update a **skill** under `.cursor/skills/` instead of (or in addition to) a hint.
